    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small card tables for playing bassette, a card game popular in Italy and France in the late 17th century and in England in the early 18th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
